Format: Verse
Glossary:
  - Term: Candâlî
    Definition: The Tibetan for Candâlî is gTum-mo, translatable as
      “mystic heat". It may be remembered that the Tibetans employed the
      “mystic heat" technique in order to keep the body physically warm
    Source: note by translator
---
Candâlî blazes at the navel,
She burns the Five Tathagatas,
She burns Locana and the others,
AHAM (=1) is burned and the Moon is melted.
